The gubernatorial candidate of Social Democratic Party (SDP), Barr. Natasha Akpoti, has called on Governor Yahaya Bello who is the candidate of the All Progressives Congress (APC) in the November 16 governorship election in Kogi State, to prepare his hand over notes. Natasha, who said this yesterday while announcing Engr. Khalid Adams Ogbeche, an Information Security Analyst, as her running mate, said the call has become necessary in view of the overall support she enjoys from the people of Kogi State who have since rejected Bello. The SDP candidate, in a statement by the spokesman of Natasha Akpoti Campaign Organisation, Odaudu Joel Minister, said they are set and by the grace of God and the support of Kogites, SDP shall win the November 16 election. Kogi guber poll: SDP candidate, Natasha serves Bello quit notice, picks running mate Kogi: SDP gov’ship candidate pledges to tackle poverty SDP gets candidate for Kogi gov’ship OVER 5,000 NIGERIAN MEN HAVE  OVERCOME POOR BEDROOM PERFORMANCE SYNDROME DUE TO THIS BRILLIANT DISCOVERY